What is this?
Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt training and certification provides foundational knowledge of Lean Six Sigma (DMAIC) and process improvement, enabling professionals to support projects or lead smaller ones. Training typically takes a few days to weeks, covering basic tools, followed by an online, often open-book exam, such as those from ASQ ($300-$400+), SSGI ($175), or CSSC. No prerequisites are required for most programs. 
Key Details for Certification
Focus: Core principles of Six Sigma, Lean concepts, and the DMAIC method.
Duration: Often 1-2 weeks of study (10-20 hours).
Exam: Typically 60-90 multiple-choice questions, often proctored.
Project Requirement: Sometimes required to apply tools in a real-world setting, though many online courses do not require it. 

